<div class="comments-head">Comments: Baby Boot Camp</div>


<div class="comments-body">
<p>Every child is different but here's my observations.</p>

<p>My daughter ( now 14 mos ) slept through the night at 8 months, and only woke once a night from 6-8 months old.</p>

<p>Two things which are paramount:<br />
1. They MUST get enough calories during the day so that hunger doesn't wake them.  This may have accounted for the long crying period.<br />
2. The must not get too much or too little sleep during the day.  Too much and they don't need a full nights rest. Too little and they become overtired ,powersleep a few hours and wake somewhat rested.</p>

<p>Hope this helps.</p>
<span class="comments-post">Posted by <a href="mailto&#58;amedlock&#64;nospam&#46;net">David Medlock</a> at June 23, 2004 03:11 PM</span>
</div>
<div class="comments-body">
<p>My son is now 1 year old and we did the sme kind of 'sleep training' around 7 months.  After a few rough days he had learned how to fall asleep on his own and ever since then we put him down at 8:00 PM, within 5 minutes he is asleap and he sleeps right through to 7:00 AM - every single ight!  Bottom line - although every child is different, you are on the right track and the payoff is well worth the effort!</p>
